Doctors who treated brain cancer sufferer Ashya King in Britain yesterday accused the boy 's parents of putting his life at risk when they refused to let him have chemotherapy .
Consultant Peter Wilson says Ashya 's chances of long-term survival could have been halved by Brett and Naghmeh King 's decision to flee abroad with him .
Dr Wilson says chemotherapy was essential to reduce the chances of the five-year-old 's cancer returning .